  "title": "Engineer (Lead) - Facilities Management",
  "description": "<ul><li>Assist Assistant Manager to manage day to day FM operations of accounts</li><li>Ensure fulfilment of scheduled commitments for FM teams</li><li>Ensure good planning and execution of service schedules</li><li>Assist in training staff members on proper work processes, operating procedures, equipment servicing, etc., and manage FM engineers’ technical competencies</li><li>Manage Staff deployment and attendance administration</li><li>Motivate site staff and ensure safe & conducive work environment</li><li>Manage customers’ expectation and deliverables and establish rapport for long term customer relationship</li><li>Manage onsite vendors and ensure timely and quality work</li><li>Provides solution proposals to clients for issues encountered onsite</li><li>Provide support to other FM site Teams for any emergency situation</li><li>Ensure continuous site improvements in areas of M&E Infrastructure, green initiatives, and operational processes</li><li>Responsible for FM Quotation submission and obtain of Vendor quotation</li><li>Ensure toolbox / daily ops meeting to be conducted c/w MOM</li><li>To provide regular support to update of the Asset Management, Risk Management, Incident Management, Weekly Report, Monthly Report and Quarterly Report</li><li>Review and provide close support to the onsite team to generate the Lifecycle replacement programme, create opportunities to meet sales revenue targets</li><li>Any other duties assigned by Assistant Manager</li></ul>",
